entry.name: HS-allow-outbound
entry.description: This is a general rule to allow trust to untrust traffic. It uses application defaults to p revent applications from running on non-default undefined ports. This is part of the App-ID support in the firew all

entry.name: HS-non-def-SSL-ports
entry.description: This is a complement to the allow-outbound rule to ensure sessions can be established and t he proper application determined. Once determined, the session will shift to the allow-outbound rule.

entry.name: HS-non-def-web-ports
entry.description: Provide visibility for non-default web browsing applications. Will provide security profile coverage and will allow based if a non-default port for the application. VISIBILITY ONLY and not app evasion.

entry.name: HS-find-non-def-apps
entry.description: This is a temporary safety net rule to find apps not on non-default ports. It still has the Gold security profile to look for threats, block bad URL's, and send files to WF.
